{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Description\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab this script mimics the behaviour of Nuendo's Edit Mode. You select an item, execute the script and move/nudge the item with the mouse. As result, the edit cursor will snap to the start of the item and follow your mouse movement.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab the script is executed as an endless loop, so you have to terminate it, when you are done. Best is, to assign it as a shortcut and terminate it when pressing the shortcut again.\sa180\par}
}

